translate ru strings:

    old "The warm desert air ran across her skin, gently waking her."
    new "The warm desert air ran across her skin, gently waking her."

    old "As she turned in her bed, she could feel the luxurious satin sheets and pillows, sliding across her body."
    new "As she turned in her bed, she could feel the luxurious satin sheets and pillows, sliding across her body."

    old "Every way she turned, it felt like the best bed she had ever slept it."
    new "Every way she turned, it felt like the best bed she had ever slept it."

    old "Sarah had thrown off the awkward outfit that had been forced on her."
    new "Sarah had thrown off the awkward outfit that had been forced on her."

    old "It was a small act of resistance to defy the man that called himself her master."
    new "It was a small act of resistance to defy the man that called himself her master."

    old "But as she pushed herself up, she wondered how much of an act of resistance it really was."
    new "But as she pushed herself up, she wondered how much of an act of resistance it really was."

    old "Instead of parading herself around in the clothes of her conqueror, she now slept naked in a bed that he owned."
    new "Instead of parading herself around in the clothes of her conqueror, she now slept naked in a bed that he owned."

    old "The room, and everything in it, was hers to use, but his by right."
    new "The room, and everything in it, was hers to use, but his by right."

    old "As she caught her own reflection in a mirror, she realized that she and her body were no exception."
    new "As she caught her own reflection in a mirror, she realized that she and her body were no exception."

    old "Like everything else in the room, it belonged to the Khan."
    new "Like everything else in the room, it belonged to the Khan."

    old "Sarah shuddered at the thought."
    new "Sarah shuddered at the thought."

    old "All her life, the idea that she was her own person hadn't even been a thought. It was just something she knew instinctively."
    new "All her life, the idea that she was her own person hadn't even been a thought. It was just something she knew instinctively."

    old "But now she was his."
    new "But now she was his."

    old "And the little freedoms afforded to her could be withdrawn whenever he pleased."
    new "And the little freedoms afforded to her could be withdrawn whenever he pleased."

    old "Sarah pulled the covers closer, a small guard against the world."
    new "Sarah pulled the covers closer, a small guard against the world."

    old "And beyond this palace, she knew her people suffered far worse than her."
    new "And beyond this palace, she knew her people suffered far worse than her."

    old "She resented her special status, even in defeat. Even if she was glad for it."
    new "She resented her special status, even in defeat. Even if she was glad for it."

    old "When finally she tired of laying in the bed, Sarah rose."
    new "When finally she tired of laying in the bed, Sarah rose."

    old "Slowly, she put on the outfit again, clasping the shackles around her waist and ankles, tying the chains together."
    new "Slowly, she put on the outfit again, clasping the shackles around her waist and ankles, tying the chains together."

    old "It covered almost nothing, which somehow felt worse than nakedness."
    new "It covered almost nothing, which somehow felt worse than nakedness."

    old "As she made her way down the hallway, she expected to hear someone, but instead everything was quiet."
    new "As she made her way down the hallway, she expected to hear someone, but instead everything was quiet."

    old "Only the soft sound of moving water, echoed in the hall."
    new "Only the soft sound of moving water, echoed in the hall."

    old "Following the sound, Sarah soon found the girl she knew as Sophia."
    new "Following the sound, Sarah soon found the girl she knew as Sophia."

    old "She sat idly by the edge of the pool, naked, running her feet back and forth through the water."
    new "She sat idly by the edge of the pool, naked, running her feet back and forth through the water."

    old "For a moment, Sarah observed the girl."
    new "For a moment, Sarah observed the girl."

    old "She seemed kind enough when they first met. But in a place like this, Sarah couldn't be entirely sure who to trust."
    new "She seemed kind enough when they first met. But in a place like this, Sarah couldn't be entirely sure who to trust."

    old "Then again, studying the girl from a distance, she didn't seem like the scheming type."
    new "Then again, studying the girl from a distance, she didn't seem like the scheming type."

    old "Maybe she was just what she appeared."
    new "Maybe she was just what she appeared."

    old "Hey."
    new "Hey."

