    new "My peoples ran cattle up and down the length of it for centuries."

    old "Free as we were, never setting roots."
    new "Free as we were, never setting roots."

    old "No empire to threaten us, cause we weren't all that important. And too quick and nimble for the Tribesmen."
    new "No empire to threaten us, cause we weren't all that important. And too quick and nimble for the Tribesmen."

    old "Till Hassar, of course."
    new "Till Hassar, of course."

    old "He read books, lots of em. And he learned all about fancy things like patterns of migration. How the water flowed and the grass followed."
    new "He read books, lots of em. And he learned all about fancy things like patterns of migration. How the water flowed and the grass followed."

    old "So he knew where we was gonna be before even we knew it."
    new "So he knew where we was gonna be before even we knew it."

    old "My folk don't fight much, so the Tribesmen didn't have much trouble."
    new "My folk don't fight much, so the Tribesmen didn't have much trouble."

    old "Sophia stood up further, her mid riff raising up above the water line."
    new "Sophia stood up further, her mid riff raising up above the water line."

